        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down.</hi> | Beckenham | <hi rend="print">Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Nov. 17<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am much pleased at your sale. I suggest, though suggestions to you on such a point are superfluous, that 3000 copies be printed.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> With my distribution &amp; copies &amp; for Review &amp; Libraries, not much more than 500 will now be left on hand.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I fear I shall not have done correcting till end of year; the corrections are frightful &amp; I think I must have another week’s rest</p>
<p>Yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 Beckenham] <hi rend="italic">before del</hi> ‘<hi rend="italic">Bromley.</hi>’ </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7372.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Murray, 16 November [1870]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7372.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Murray, 16 November [1870]</ref>. Murray had proposed to print 2500 copies of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> (<ref target="./DCP-LETT-7329.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Murray, 28 September [1870]</ref>). In February 1871, 2500 copies were printed, with a second issue of 2000 in March (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2661.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">R. B. Freeman 1977</ref>, p. 129).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">There are eighty names on CD’s presentation list for <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> (see DAR 210.11: 32 and <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 19, Appendix IV).</note>
        </div>        
            
